  "text": "For hip joints, the maximum pressure generated during daily activities on the hip joint has been estimated at 12 MPa in acetabular cups [CITATION_1] . By considering a factor of safety of two, the maximum pressure used in this study was 25 MPa. (The load on the sample was calculated from Hertzian contact pressure, which was developed at the contact point between the femoral head and acetabular cups.) In some reported studies, expected pressure was approximated to a very high value of 375 MPa, to accelerate the expected wear events (4) (5) .",
